cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper deals with the problem of signal reconstruction from non-linear measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses applications of the proposed method in compressed sensing and auto-encoder, which further supports the relevance of the above-mentioned sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
